11. bxc3 Bxc3 
12. Rab1! } { Another piece is developed. How many pieces does Black have in the game? White has five! And the king is safe! And the center is in White's hands. Black is not developed, the king is not castled, and the bishop on c3 is almost stuck. All of that is worth much more than one pawn. } dxc4 ( { • } 12...O-O { It is too late to castle kingside. White can win the bishop on c3. For example, } 13.Be7!? Re8 14.Bd6 Nd7 15.Rb3 dxc4 16.Bh7+!? Kh8 17.Rxc3+- ) ( { • } 12...Bb4 { Here are some interesting lines that lead to a win for White. } 13.c5!? { The bishop shall not pass! } 13...b6 14.a3!? Qxa3 { 14...Bxa3 15.Rb3 15.Ra1+- 15...bxc5 16.Ra1 c4 17.Rbxa3 cxd3 18.Qb2 Qc7 19.Bg3+- } 15.Rb3 Qa4 16.Qb2 bxc5 { 16...a5 17.Ra1+- } 17.dxc5 Bxc5 18.Qxg7+- ) 
13. Bxc4 Bb4 
14. Ne5! } { Once you developed all your pieces you need to launch the attack. The knight on e5 is now putting pressure on the pawns not only the squares. } Bd6 ( 14...Nd7 15.Ng6!? { That is one interesting idea! } 15...fxg6 { 15...Rg8 16.f4+- The last piece is joining the attack. } 16.Qxg6+ Kf8 17.Bxe6+- ) 
15. f4! { Magnus is preparing to open another file for the rook. Sometimes you can push the pawn in front of your rook instead of moving it some place. } Qc7 ( 15...O-O { Here is how White could coordinate all the pieces in one attack. } 16.f5!? exf5 { 16...Bxe5 17.fxe6! Bxe6 18.Bxe6 fxe6 19.Rxf8+ Kxf8 20.Qh7+- } 17.Nxf7! Rxf7 18.Rxb7! Bxb7 19.Rxf5! { That is one fantastic geometry! } 19...Qc7 20.Rxf7 Qxf7 21.Bxf7+ Kxf7 22.Qb3++- { The geometrical magic continues. } ) 
16. Qe4 { The queen comes closer. } ( { • } 16.f5+- { This line was better. } ) ( { • } 16.Nxf7! Qxf7 17.f5+- { Even this was winning. } ) b6 { The time has come! All the pieces are ready! } ( { • The last chance was to somewhat close the position } 16...f5 17.Qf3+- ) ( { • } 16...O-O { The strongest would be } 17.Nxf7!! { 17.f5+- } 17...Qxf7 18.f5+- { White is breaking through! } ) 
17. Nxf7! ( 17.f5+- ) Qxf7 ( 17...Kxf7 18.f5+- { With a deadly attack. } ) 
18. f5! } { White has an overwhelming attacking advantage. } Qh5 ( 18...O-O 19.fxe6+- { The e-pawn will decide the game. } ) 
19. Bxe6!? Nd7 
20. f6!? { White is just going forward and there is nothing Black can do about it! } Nxf6 ( 20...gxf6 21.Bg4++- { Wins the queen. } ) 
21. Rxf6! Qxh4 ( 21...gxf6 22.Bg4++- { With a winning discovered check. } ) 
22. Qxc6+! } Ke7 
23. Rf7+! } Kxe6 
