1. d4 } { We are going to look at this game from Black's perspective. } Nf6 } { Developing the knight while preventing e2-e4. } 
2. c4 e6 } { Preparing the development of the bishop. } 
3. Nc3 Bb4 } { Developing the bishop while still preventing e2-e4. } 
4. Nf3 ( 4.e4? Nxe4 $17 { Black wins the pawn due to the pin. } ) O-O { Castle! Black castled literally as quickly as possible! } 
5. Bg5 c5 { Black is fighting for the center. } 
6. e3 cxd4 
7. Qxd4 { One risky decision! Usually, it is not good to develop the queen like that. } ( 7.exd4 d5 8.Bd3= { White would be ok after this. } ) Nc6 } { Developing the knight with a tempo! } 
8. Qd3 { White king stayed in the center and Ding is taking immediate action! No hesitation! } h6! { It is usually good to ask the bishop how he is doing. This way, it would have to either take the knight (that would give us two bishops), let go of the pin (Bf4. This way we would not have to worry about it), or maintain the pin with Bh4 (this way we would have an option of g7-g5 at our disposal). } 
9. Bh4 d5!? { The pawn goes to the center. For now, the position is still balanced. } 
10. Rd1 g5!? { This move lets go of the pin and kicks the bishop. The downside is that the king on g8 would be vulnerable to attack. } 
11. Bg3 { When playing g7-g5 (or g2-g4) one has to watch out for the sacrifice. } ( 11.Nxg5? hxg5 12.Bxg5 { The king is exposed and the pin gets stronger. In this case, Black could handle the pin with } 12...Be7 $17 ) Ne4!? } { Black is trying to exploit the pin with the knight that just got liberated from a similar problem. This move does move the knight again in the opening. Black could afford that because White lost some time with all those queen moves. } ( 11...Qa5!? { Developing the queen was also a decent idea. } ) 
12. Nd2 ( { White is trying to unpin. } 12.Be2 Bxc3+!? 13.bxc3 Qa5 $15 { White's queenside is in trouble. } ) Nc5!? } { Kicking the queen again! } 
13. Qc2 d4! { Hitting the center! Black is trying to clear the way towards that king. } 
14. Nf3 } { Another pawn goes to the center! The bishop is ready to join the fight. } 
