2. Bg5 } { The pseudo-Trompowsky. } Nf6 { With this move we transpose back to a normal Trompowsky (1.d4 Nf6 2.Bg5). Now White will usually exchange on f6. } 
3. Bxf6 exf6 } { Making space for the development of our bishop. } 
4. e3 Bd6 } { Black will castle and complete the development. One of the good setups for Black would be f5+Nb8-d7-f6+Be6, etc. }
