1. Moving the knight from f6 to exchange the bishops. After that, Black's development would become much easier. The knight could go to e4, g4, or h5 depending on White's actions.

2. Developing the bishop to g4 or e6, although Black has to watch out for the Nf3-e5 jump followed by f2-f4.

3. g7-g6, followed by Nf8-e6 (Black has to play g7-g6 to not lose the h7 pawn).

